    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-11-18T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-11-18T15:00:00-05:00" n="340"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d340">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3231/1075: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Frost</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-11-18T17:00:00-03:00"
                            >November 18, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 18—3:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>295. My 292, November 14, 4 p.m. The President of the Chamber of Deputies, in
                    accordance with constitutional requirements, has just promulgated our trade
                    agreement.</p>
                <p>As soon as arrangements are completed will cable Department for final
                    authorization with respect to exchange of ratifications which will probably be
                    effected by Ambassador Gibson who arrives Thursday morning.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Frost</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
